title: Walt Whitman to William Michael Rossetti, 11 February 1876
text: Walt Whitman to William Rossetti1963431 Stevens st.Streetcor West.Camden,N.New Jersey,U.S. America. Feb.February 11 / 761876W. M.William Michael Rossetti:My dear friend,I would ask of you the favor to see, if convenient, whether the enclosed article (The American War) would be available for the Academy—(or any where else if you think preferable.) I would like pay for it—would be satisfied with 25, or $30. I am getting along much the same. My new book wontwon't be out yet, publicly, for a month. Walt Whitman I also send a little hitherto unpublished poem, The Man-of-War Bird—which I can't sell here—I wonder if you could sell it for me, in London? It is not in my new book, & is entirely fresh. Walt Whitman to William Michael Rossetti, 11 February 1876
